FBIS4-32196 "dreeu120_k_94009" FBIS-EEU-94-120 Daily Report 21 Jun 1994 CROATIA Canadian Soldier Killed, 2 Wounded by Mine Canadian Soldier Killed, 2 Wounded by Mine LD2106210294 Montreal Radio Canada International in English 2030 GMT 21 Jun 94 LD2106210294 Montreal Radio Canada International English BFN [Excerpt] A Canadian peacekeeper was killed in Croatia today [21st June] and two others were wounded. Thirty-one year old Corporal Mark Robert Isfield of Chillawack, British Columbia, died when a landmine exploded under his armored vehicle. Thirty-one year old Sergeant Paul Macmillan of Calgary, Alberta, and 35-year old Sergeant Gregory Paul James, also of Chillawack, were injured in the explosion. [passage omitted]
